The paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms for two-player zero-sum Markov games, which involves both machine learning and game theory concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
